<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER AUTOMATE-2 - REMOVE - INPUT SHAFT</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="2">
        <title>INPUT SHAFT</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the four cap retaining bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302262">Figure 62</hotlnk>). Pull the shaft from the housing. It may be helpful to
                place two bolts in the threaded bearing cap holes. Tightening the bolts will draw the bearing cap from
                the housing. Tap the input shaft out of the bearing cap.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302262" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302262" filename="../figg13/G1302262.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 62. Input Shaft Removal</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302263">Figure 63</hotlnk>). Press the bearing off the shaft.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>When pressing bearings, use a shield to protect people from possible flying parts.</para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f1302263" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302263" filename="../figg13/G1302263.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 63. Remove Snap Ring</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
